Peter Stephenson wrote:
> Yes, I thought of that.  Here's an attempt.  It seems to work, according
> to lsof.

I missed the case where all 10 fd's are already used, in which case the
pipe's descriptors leak.  Add

	if (i < tmppipe[0])
	    close(tmppipe[0]);
	if (i < tmppipe[1])
	    close(tmppipe[1]);

and stir.

